Bijit Web page














BIJIT HORE 
(Research
Staff)
I am a member of the Information Systems Group (ISG) in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
Science at University of California, Irvine.
I primarily collaborate with Prof. Sharad Mehrotra and Prof. Nalini Venkatasubramanian.
Research
Interests: 
My research focuses on
privacy-preservation and disclosure-control in data outsourcing, data mining
and pervasive-space applications. My broader research interest spans relational
& geo-spatial data management, data mining, distributed systems, graph
theory and combinatorial optimization.
Recent Publications:
 
New! IndexingEncrypted Documents for Supporting Efficient Keyword Search
(Secure Data Management Workshop, VLDB 2012)
Bijit Hore,
Mamadou H. Diallo,
Ee-Chien Chang, Sharad Mehrotra.
 
New! CloudProtect: Managing Data Privacy in Cloud
Applications (accepted for publication in IEEE CLOUD, 2012)
Mamadou H. Diallo, Bijit Hore, Ee-Chien
Chang, Sharad Mehrotra, Nalini Venkatasubramanian.
 
